  ],
  "text": "The key C++ source files defining Chromium's multi-process architecture are:\n\n1. **RenderProcessHostImpl** (`content/browser/renderer_host/render_process_host_impl.h`): This is the browser-side representation of a renderer process. The class RenderProcessHostImpl (defined at line 195) implements RenderProcessHost and manages communication with the renderer process through IPC/Mojo interfaces. It also implements mojom::RendererHost for browser-to-renderer control messages.\n\n2. **BrowserMainLoop** (`content/browser/browser_main_loop.h` and `content/browser/browser_main_loop.cc`): This defines the main browser process event loop. The BrowserMainLoop class (defined at line 106 in the header) manages the primary message loop and spawns various worker threads. It is responsible for initializing and shutting down various browser subsystems.\n\n3. **RenderThreadImpl** (`content/renderer/render_thread_impl.h` and `content/renderer/render_thread_impl.cc`): This is the main thread implementation of a renderer process. The RenderThreadImpl class (defined at line 126 in the header) represents the main thread where blink::WebView instances live. It inherits from RenderThread, ChildThreadImpl, and implements the mojom::Renderer interface.\n\n4. **ChildProcessLauncher** (`content/browser/child_process_launcher.h`): This class (defined at line 212) is responsible for spawning child processes asynchronously. It manages the process launch lifecycle and notifies clients when processes are launched or fail to launch through its Client interface.\n\n5. **Renderer (Mojom Interface)** (`content/common/renderer.mojom`): This Mojo interface (defined at line 49) is the primordial Channel-associated interface implemented by a render process. It serves as the mechanism for browser-to-renderer control messages that need to retain FIFO ordering with respect to legacy IPC messages.\n\nThese files collectively define Chromium's multi-process architecture: the browser process (BrowserMainLoop) spawns renderer processes (via ChildProcessLauncher), each with a RenderThreadImpl main thread. The processes communicate through Mojo interfaces (Renderer interface) and are managed by RenderProcessHostImpl on the browser side."
}

